{"article_id":"Rp6OOwVB10M8AjJS","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The number of coronavirus cases in New York surged by more than 4,500 on Saturday ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"jolting the statewide number of infected past 11,600 on the eve of an unprecedented lockdown from Brooklyn to Buffalo","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"aimed at containing the deadly bug .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"New York City ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"which remained the epicenter of the nation ' s COVID-19 crisis ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"accounted for the bulk of the alarming increase .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"More than 2,400 new cases were reported in the Big Apple ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"raising the total number of sick to 8,115 ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"city officials said .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"The virus killed at least 15 more people in the city on Saturday ,","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"officials said ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"bringing the death toll to 60 .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"The day before , COVID-19 claimed 14 lives between 10 a.m. and 6 p.m. , a troubling rate of more than one an hour .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"The statewide coronavirus death toll meanwhile exceeded 70 .","depth":4},{"id":14,"text":"Nationwide , there were more than 25,000 cases with 300 deaths , data","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Johns Hopkins University revealed Saturday ,","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"as New Jersey joined four other states","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"- New York , California , Illinois and Connecticut -","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"in imposing restrictions on movement","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"to stop the spread of the virus .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"In response to the mounting crisis","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"- and the expectation","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that the grim numbers will continue to rise exponentially-","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"Gov . Andrew Cuomo promised to purchase 6,000 new ventilators and two million virus-blocking N95 masks .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"A million of the masks will be sent to health care responders in the city ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"and 500,000 would go to Long Island ,","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"\" We are literally scouring the globe","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"looking for medical supplies , \"","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"he said in a press conference .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"Hospitals statewide have been directed to end elective surgeries and alter their space and staffing","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"to accommodate the flood of infected .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"\" We are now working with hospitals","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"to reconfigure space","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"to get more beds","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"and find more staff","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"to manage the beds , '","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"Cuomo said .","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"New York is also reviewing four possible locations for temporary \" field hospitals , \"","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"to be set up by the Army Corps of Engineers","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"and operated with FEMA assistance ,","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"Cuomo said .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"The four sites","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"being mulled","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"are the city ' s Javits Center , SUNY Stony Brook , SUNY Westbury and the Westchester Convention Center .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"The Javits Center could be turned into a 1,000-patient hospital in the next few days ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Cuomo said .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"The Army Corps has also been eyeing empty hotels and college dorms as potential medical space .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"And the Navy still intends to send the USS Comfort to New York Harbor in the next few weeks ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"where overflow , non-coronavirus hospital cases would be treated .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"New York ' s goal is to increase the state ' s number of hospital beds from the current 50,000 up to 70,000 .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"Shoring up existing hospital space","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"- and building more -","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"is vital .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"Some 15 percent of the state ' s sick have required some hospitalization","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"- so far about 1,600 people .","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"see also","depth":4},{"id":57,"text":"Cuomo orders lockdown ,","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"shuts down non-essential businesses","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"Gov . Andrew Cuomo ordered a statewide lockdown as New York ...","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"In New York City , 1,160 people have required hospitalization ,","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"including 260 in an ICU .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"\" Every piston is firing , \"","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"Cuomo said .","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"\" Everything","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"that can be done","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"will be done . \"","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"The governor continued urging all but essential workers to stay home ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"or at least stay apart .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"A lockdown","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"that takes effect 8 p.m. Sunday night","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"will set tight limits on how New Yorkers shop , work , and play - all","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"designed to minimize close contact","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"and prevent a healthcare-system-crippling spike in cases .","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"That means all New Yorkers , even the young ,","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"the governor said ,","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"flatly telling young people","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"who think","depth":15},{"id":78,"text":"they have immunity to the deadly bug :","depth":15},{"id":79,"text":"\" You are wrong . \"","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"Just over half of the state ' s coronavirus patients","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"- 54 percent -","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"are 18 to 49 years old .","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"\" You can get this virus","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"and you can transfer the virus","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"and you can wind up hurting someone","depth":16},{"id":86,"text":"who you love ,","depth":16},{"id":87,"text":"or hurting someone wholly inadvertently , \"","depth":15},{"id":88,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"Social distancing is vital","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"to slow down the growth of contagion","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"so that the state does not exhaust its medical personnel or its supply of ventilators , protective garb , and hospital space .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"\" We ' re trying to reduce the spread to over a period of months , \"","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"Cuomo explained in a press conference .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"\" Over a period of months , our health care system can deal with the numbers . \"","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"In some encouraging news the number of cases in Westchester","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"- where the state ' s first major outbreak was located -","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"is slowing .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"\" That is good news , \"","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"the governor said ,","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"proof","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"that the original \" containment zone \" is working .","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"Still , there were at least 294 cases there as of Saturday .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"In New Jersey , Gov . Phil Murphy signed an executive order","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"directing most residents to stay home .","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"Jersey ' s sick tally rose to 1,327 Saturday , with 16 deaths .","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"That ' s up from 890 cases and 11 deaths on Friday .","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"Both Murphy and Cuomo attributed their states ' hikes in reported infections on increased testing .","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"\" No one is spiking any footballs ,","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"but we have been ahead of the curve on testing , \"","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"Murphy said .","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"Further jangling area nerves ,","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"all flights were briefly suspended Saturday afternoon at airports from Philadelphia to Westchester","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"after an air traffic controller trainee","depth":15},{"id":114,"text":"who was stationed at the FAA ' s New York Air Route Traffic Control Center in Ronkonkoma","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"tested positive for the virus .","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"The center ,","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"which handles high-altitude flights and flyovers ,","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"was shut for a deep cleaning .","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"Sunday night ' s lockdown will force the shutdown of most of the state ' s businesses , with the exception of grocery stores and bodegas , liquor stores , gas stations , laundromats and restaurant delivery services .","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"The city has appointed a \" Food Czar , \" Kathryn Garcia ,","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"to ensure","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"no one goes hungry ,","depth":15},{"id":123,"text":"Mayor Bill de Blasio said .","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"Those lucky enough","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"to still be working in \" non-essential \" businesses","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"must do so from home ;","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"and exercising out of doors was limited to such solitary , non-team endeavors as walking , biking and running .","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"Saturday ' s sunny , low-50s weather drew crowds of New Yorkers","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"- all eager to shake off the self-isolation blues -","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"to the city ' s parks and beaches .","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"\" You should send these pictures to Cuomo ,","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"this place is too crowded , \"","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"one Central Park-goer shouted to a Post photographer on a west side foot path .","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"\" I wanted to do something today with my friends , \"","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"Matt Johnson , 42 , said of a birthday party","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"he held on the sands of Rockaway beach .","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"Seven pals brought surfboards , a small vanilla cake and a can of Lysol .","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"\" It ' s kinda like your last meal on death row , \"","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"agreed Devin Romeo , 28 ,","depth":15},{"id":140,"text":"who was surfing nearby .","depth":15},{"id":141,"text":"\" You are out in the sun","depth":15},{"id":142,"text":"and getting your last wave in","depth":16},{"id":143,"text":"and its bitter-sweet . \"","depth":16},{"id":144,"text":"In Washington Square Park , the virus couldn ' t slow down chess players such as Sarfaraz Ahmed .","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"\" How long are you going to be in prison in your own house ? \"","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"he asked .","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"\" I ' ll take my chances . \"","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"Additional reporting by Georgett Roberts , Rosemary Misdary , Sam Raskin and Bernadette Hogan and Post Wires","depth":1}],"relations":[{"parent":297,"left":296,"right":148,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":168,"right":295,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":161,"right":167,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":151,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":0,"right":150,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":156,"right":159,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":156,"left":153,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"le